Lectures and practical classes address the principles and possibilities of rehabilitation in various disorders: disorders and diseases of the support and movement system, brain damage, oncology, cardiovascular diseases. They learn to objectively evaluate various functional impairments, learn about the work of different team profiles. Case studies and various evidence-based treatment options are addressed.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide knowledge about principles and possibilities of rehabilitation in case of various functional disorders, to introduce The work of various members of the team (rehab, physiotherapist, occupational therapist, psychologist, speech therapist) and various methods of treatment.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  It is oriented towards rehabilitation as a team specialist. Knows the principles of assessing patient functional reserves, and is able to evaluate the most common functional disorders and to prepare a rehabilitation plan.Approaches to rehabilitation in the case of various functional disorders
